I think the answer is actually pretty straightforward.  It's trivial to go from a serial to a threaded server.  It's way harder to write an event-based server using poll or select.<p>Serially:<p><pre><code>  int handle_connection(int fd) {
    ...
  }

  int loop() {
    ...
    while(1) {
      fd = accept(listener);
      handle_connection(fd);
    }
  }
</code></pre>
Threaded:<p><pre><code>  int handle_connection(int fd) {
    ...
  }

  int loop() {
    ...
    while(1) {
      fd = accept(listener);
      thread_start(handle_connection, fd);
    }
  }</code></pre>
